commit.message: Document changes in CHANGES and release 1.3.0

Bug-fix behaviour when 1 wrong PID was given - all other (valid) PIDs would run into error

- reset errno in print_process() before querying the actual process
- errno will be set later by various syscalls
Document that syscall_magic.h is obsolete and remove dependecy from Makefile

Remove installation instructions about building without affinity

- no longer supported

Pretty up definition of char[] for cpu affinity strings by providing macro CPUSET_HEXSTRING(name)

- will allocate enough space to hold the hex strings resulting from calling cpuset_to_str()
- replace all variable definitions with macro

Fully implement new cpu_set_t for setting and querying affinity

- add cpuset_to_str() and str_to_cpuset() functions from util-linux, and use
- rewrite debugging sections to be OK again

Compile schedtool with affinity support per default

- take out all #ifdef HAVE_AFFINITY in schedtool.c
- revisit Makefile and remove affinity + no_affinity targets

Make schedtool compile again w/ cpu_set_t API, part II
- make print_process use cpu_set_t for sched_getaffinity()
